author: jdonnerstag
msg: You may now call getBodyContainer() any time from WebPage or AbstractAjaxBehavior to attach an AttributeModifier to the container. A convinience method getBodyContainer().addOnLoadAttributeModifer() adds an appending attribute modifier to the onLoad attribute. IBodyOnLoadContributor has been removed.

The BodyContainer is no longer autoAdded by a resolver, instead WebPage's constructor adds it if a body tag is in the markup. This change makes it even possible to replace the default body container with your own.
